Malaysian health authorities have raised concerns about a growing number of coronavirus deaths and serious cases involving children, after a surge in overall infections forced the Southeast Asian nation into a strict lockdown. New Zealand is pushing Asia-Pacific trade group APEC to remove all tariffs on Covid-19 vaccines and related medical products, but is facing opposition from some members who believe the plan is too ambitious, people familiar with discussions said. Johnson & Johnson said on Friday that it has been in talks with Taiwan about providing its Covid-19 vaccine to the island since last year. "Johnson & Johnson has been in confidential discussions with the Taiwan Government regarding supply of the Johnson & Johnson Covid-19 vaccine since last year," it said in an emailed statement to Reuters, without giving details. Reuters Before heading to the airport for a new life in Israel, some of the 40 members of the Bnei Menashe community from India's north-eastern Manipur state tested positive for Covid-19, delaying a homecoming 2,700 years in the making. The White House laid out a plan for the United States to share 25 million surplus COVID-19 vaccine doses with other countries.